==English==

===Etymology===
From Old English [[glidan]]

===Pronunciation===
* [[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|IPA]]: /ɡlɑɪd/ (/ɡlɑɪdz/, /ɡlɑɪdɪŋ/, /ɡlɑɪdəd/)
* [[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|SAMPA]]: /<tt>glaId</tt>/ (/<tt>glaIdz</tt>/, /<tt>glaIdIN</tt>/, /<tt>glaId@d</tt>/)
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪd|-aɪd]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of gliding.
# {{linguistics}} [[semivowel|Semivowel]]
# {{fencing}} An attack or preparatory movement made by sliding down the opponent’s [[blade]], keeping it in constant contact.

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-verb|glid|ing}}

# To move softly, smoothly, or effortlessly.
# To fly unpowered, as of an aircraft.

====Synonyms====
(''to move effortlessly'')
* [[coast]]
* [[slide]]

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|glid|ing}}

# To cause to glide.

